  <h1 class="page-title">How to Contribute</h1>
  <p class="page-lead">Atmos is open source and welcomes contributions of all kinds — bug fixes, features, design improvements, or documentation.</p>

  <h2 id="before-you-start">Before You Start</h2>
  <p>
    Check the <a href="https://github.com/S-P-H-E/Atmos/issues" target="_blank">open issues</a> before starting work
    to avoid duplicating effort. If you want to build something new, open an issue first to discuss the approach.
  </p>

  <h2 id="workflow">Contribution Workflow</h2>

  <div class="steps">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">1</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3>Fork the repository</h3>
        <p>Click <strong>Fork</strong> on GitHub to create your own copy of Atmos under your account.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">2</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3>Create a feature branch</h3>
        <div class="code-block terminal">
          <div class="code-header">
            <span class="code-lang">bash</span>
            <button class="code-copy"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="9" y="9" width="13" height="13" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M5 15H4a2 2 0 01-2-2V4a2 2 0 012-2h9a2 2 0 012 2v1"/></svg> Copy</button>
          </div>
          <pre><code>git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">3</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3>Make your changes</h3>
        <p>Follow the existing code style. Keep commits small and focused with descriptive messages.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">4</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3>Submit a pull request</h3>
        <p>Open a PR against the <code>main</code> branch with a clear description of what you changed and why.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="code-style">Code Style</h2>
  <p>
    Atmos uses <strong>ESLint</strong> and <strong>Prettier</strong> for consistent formatting.
    Run <code>npm run lint</code> before submitting. PRs with lint errors won't be merged.
  </p>

